WEBVTT

00:01.167 --> 00:03.127
(BEEPING)

00:12.595 --> 00:14.596
(ELECTRICAL BUZZING)

00:42.792 --> 00:44.334
(ZAPPING)

00:44.836 --> 00:46.837
(MANIACAL LAUGHTER)

00:46.880 --> 00:48.005
Huh?

00:48.548 --> 00:49.798
Oh.

00:50.425 --> 00:52.426
Ha-ha-ha-ha!

00:57.223 --> 00:58.807
(HAWAIIAN MUSIC)

01:05.230 --> 01:06.356
(GROWLS)

01:06.816 --> 01:08.484
(SCREAMING)

01:09.444 --> 01:12.112
- Aloha.
- What?

01:13.573 --> 01:15.407
STITCH: Bye-bye.

01:19.287 --> 01:20.287
(COUGHS)

01:20.872 --> 01:22.790
(LAUGHS)

01:37.972 --> 01:40.808
Stitch, why are you doing this?

01:42.435 --> 01:43.685
Ah-ha-ha-ha-ha!

01:43.895 --> 01:45.187
Please stop.

01:51.361 --> 01:52.778
(GROWLS)

01:52.862 --> 01:53.862
(GASPS)

01:56.783 --> 01:58.784
Stop it, Stitch. Don't...

02:01.788 --> 02:03.997
No! Stitch!

02:04.082 --> 02:07.126
Wake up! Wake up!

02:07.168 --> 02:09.794
Wake up, Stitch. Wake up.

02:09.838 --> 02:12.214
Stitch, wake up.

02:12.298 --> 02:15.801
It's all right. Don't worry.

02:15.844 --> 02:19.221
You were just having
another nightmare.

02:19.305 --> 02:22.641
- Seems like a bad one.
- (MUTTERS IN ALIEN LANGUAGE)

02:22.851 --> 02:25.060
You know what this means, don't you?

02:25.186 --> 02:29.398
Hmm. Very interesting.

02:29.482 --> 02:31.316
Why don't you tell me
what happened next?

02:31.359 --> 02:33.986
Well...
(MUTTERS IN ALIEN LANGUAGE)

02:34.028 --> 02:35.821
(MIMICS EXPLOSION)

02:35.864 --> 02:39.074
- Mmm, I see.
- Then... (MIMICS MACHINE GUN)

02:39.159 --> 02:41.577
And then... (SHRIEKING)

02:41.661 --> 02:43.328
And then... (GASPS)

02:43.830 --> 02:46.832
That's it. No more.

02:46.875 --> 02:52.087
It's my professional opinion
that you're afraid of turning bad again.

02:52.172 --> 02:54.506
We need to test your goodness level.

02:54.549 --> 02:59.178
For example, someone bad would
let this Elvis Blue Hawaii lamp,

02:59.220 --> 03:04.057
circa 1971,
smash to pieces against that wall.

03:04.517 --> 03:09.271
Or let my favorite book,
Plastic Surgeries Gone Wrong,

03:09.355 --> 03:11.732
drop out this window to be lost forever.

03:11.816 --> 03:13.567
Yah! Waagh!

03:15.361 --> 03:20.824
Or let his family member
fall to her painful, crushing death.

03:20.867 --> 03:22.868
No!

03:22.911 --> 03:26.955
See?
Look at all the good things you did.

03:27.040 --> 03:30.375
My prognosis?
Your goodness level is extra high.

03:31.586 --> 03:33.086
Nothing to worry about.

03:35.381 --> 03:38.300
WOMAN: Lilo! Stitch!
You're gonna be late for hula class.

03:38.384 --> 03:39.718
Except that.

03:40.220 --> 03:41.220
(ELECTRIC BUZZING)

03:44.224 --> 03:45.724
- LILO: Stitch!
- (GASPS)

03:47.227 --> 03:49.061
Hurry up, you two.

03:49.103 --> 03:52.731
Hey, can you guys help me today?
It's family night.

03:52.774 --> 03:55.400
- I want the house clean.
- Not me.

03:55.443 --> 03:59.154
I have very important project
I've been working on.

03:59.239 --> 04:01.281
- No more crop circles!
- Ah!

04:01.366 --> 04:04.409
Oh... All the other aliens
get to make them.

04:04.494 --> 04:08.580
- What about you?
- I have a full day of Earth research.

04:08.665 --> 04:11.416
Watching talk shows
and reading magazines?

04:11.459 --> 04:13.293
Yeah, it takes it out of ya.

04:13.378 --> 04:15.671
Can we take the hovercraft? Please?

04:15.755 --> 04:19.341
It's too dangerous.
Besides, someone may see you.

04:19.425 --> 04:21.593
- Please?
- Please?

04:22.262 --> 04:26.014
All right,
you can take it if you can find it.

04:26.099 --> 04:27.432
Yes!

04:27.475 --> 04:29.977
I hid it so good this time, they're never...

04:30.061 --> 04:32.688
Thanks, Nani.

04:32.772 --> 04:36.191
Aw! I gotta find
a better hiding place for that thing.

04:36.776 --> 04:38.944
STITCH: Whoa! Whoa!

04:40.363 --> 04:42.531
There's no place I'd rather be

04:42.615 --> 04:44.408
(CHORUS IN HAWAIIAN)

04:44.450 --> 04:47.786
Lingering in the ocean blue

04:48.871 --> 04:50.664
Oops. Sorry!

04:50.748 --> 04:53.709
I'd surf till the sun sets
beyond the horizon

04:57.630 --> 05:02.801
Flying by
on a Hawaiian rollercoaster ride

05:05.596 --> 05:09.641
(CHORUS IN HAWAIIAN)

05:16.607 --> 05:18.608
(LAUGHS)

05:19.986 --> 05:21.987
- (BOTH LAUGHING)
- Hawaiian rollercoaster ride

05:22.030 --> 05:25.574
There's no place I'd rather be

05:29.871 --> 05:32.914
Girls, I have very exciting news.

05:32.999 --> 05:35.584
This week is our May Day...

05:35.668 --> 05:38.337
Sorry I'm late. But wait till you see this.

05:38.421 --> 05:40.922
I got my 'uli'uli technique down.

05:41.007 --> 05:43.175
- Lilo...
- Kui kala laima!

05:43.885 --> 05:45.302
Ho kee ma!

05:45.970 --> 05:47.888
Uliuli, uliuli, ha!

05:47.972 --> 05:49.806
- Lilo?
- Uliuli, uliuli, ha!

05:50.975 --> 05:51.975
Uliuli, uliuli, ha!

05:52.393 --> 05:54.519
Lilo, we're not doing that today.

05:54.604 --> 05:56.605
We're not doing that today.

05:58.566 --> 06:00.275
Nyah-nyah-nyah-nyah,
nyah-nyah-nyah.

06:00.735 --> 06:01.735
Bleugh!

06:02.111 --> 06:03.111
(GROWLS)

06:03.529 --> 06:05.864
Kumu has an announcement.

06:05.907 --> 06:10.660
In three days
is our town's May Day celebration.

06:10.703 --> 06:12.454
And here's the best part.

06:12.538 --> 06:15.248
There will be a hula competition.

06:15.333 --> 06:17.876
Each of you will create an original hula.

06:17.960 --> 06:21.546
The one that
best expresses the aloha spirit

06:21.631 --> 06:24.216
will lead our halau
as the winning dance.

06:24.550 --> 06:25.842
You, you, you!

06:25.885 --> 06:28.887
- Are there any questions?
- Kumu, I have one.

06:29.138 --> 06:33.141
Will people who are late to class
be allowed to participate?

06:33.226 --> 06:37.729
Mertle, I think in the spirit of aloha,
we should be tolerant of others.

06:37.814 --> 06:39.856
Well, there's no harm in asking.

06:39.899 --> 06:45.320
I want you to use class time today
to begin working on your ideas.

06:45.405 --> 06:47.906
The May Day celebration is big time.

06:47.949 --> 06:49.658
The whole town will be there.

06:49.742 --> 06:51.910
Maybe I'll get a contract.

06:51.953 --> 06:55.789
We can do any idea we want.
Even make our own costumes.

06:55.873 --> 06:57.958
- Cool!
- It'll be a lot of work.

06:58.042 --> 07:00.544
My mom knows
how to make great costumes.

07:00.586 --> 07:02.629
My mom can sew really good.

07:02.713 --> 07:05.799
My mom knows a lot about hula.
She can help me with it.

07:05.883 --> 07:08.802
- I guess Lilo's on her own.
- She doesn't have a mom.

07:08.886 --> 07:11.304
- Don't say that.
- It's the truth.

07:11.389 --> 07:14.808
- Not everyone has a mom.
- All right, don't bite my head off.

07:14.892 --> 07:17.436
I don't know
what costume I'm gonna wear.

07:18.604 --> 07:21.106
Lilo, may I speak with you?

07:24.527 --> 07:27.279
This is a book of past winners.

07:27.613 --> 07:29.614
Do you know who this is?

07:30.616 --> 07:32.409
It's your mother.

07:32.994 --> 07:35.203
- My mom?
- Aye.

07:35.288 --> 07:38.457
She won the competition
when she was your age.

07:38.541 --> 07:43.962
She was as beautiful as an orchid
and as graceful as a rolling wave.

07:45.756 --> 07:48.216
Here. To inspire you.

07:50.803 --> 07:52.762
Mmm.

07:53.723 --> 07:55.140
That's my mom.

07:55.266 --> 07:58.435
She won the competition
when she was my age.

08:01.731 --> 08:03.565
Yay!

08:05.985 --> 08:07.486
Hey, Lilo.

08:07.612 --> 08:12.657
Maybe your dog can take a picture
of me when I win the competition.

08:12.825 --> 08:16.369
- How do you know you'll win?
- It's pretty well known

08:16.454 --> 08:19.581
that I'm the best dancer
in the seven-year-old division.

08:19.665 --> 08:22.709
I don't know. I think maybe I can win.

08:22.793 --> 08:23.877
Hello?

08:23.961 --> 08:28.006
You're a stinky dancer, and anything
you come up with will be stinky.

08:28.382 --> 08:30.008
- Oh!
- Uh-uh.

08:30.259 --> 08:33.511
You'll never be like your mom. Never.

08:34.889 --> 08:37.057
- Okay.
- That's it!

08:37.308 --> 08:38.642
Smile.

08:38.683 --> 08:40.852
(SCREAMING)

08:40.977 --> 08:43.020
(CAMERA SHUTTER)

08:45.858 --> 08:49.694
As you can see,
there was a little disagreement...

08:50.696 --> 08:52.489
- Again.
- Ai-ya.

08:52.907 --> 08:54.866
Next time, flush the evidence.

08:54.992 --> 08:56.201
Ka-shush.

08:56.369 --> 09:00.163
Why don't you come inside, Kumu?
Excuse the mess.

09:00.206 --> 09:01.206
KUMU: Ooh-we.

09:01.874 --> 09:03.625
We have a full house.

09:03.709 --> 09:07.546
Make yourself at home, Kumu.
I just made some lemonade.

09:07.630 --> 09:09.214
- Wha...
- Hey!

09:09.257 --> 09:11.299
Nani, we're out of lemonade.

09:11.384 --> 09:13.510
Pleakley, I just made that.

09:13.970 --> 09:17.556
Nani. You have to come to lab
and see my new invention.

09:17.640 --> 09:19.057
I just mopped in here!

09:19.100 --> 09:21.768
It will improve your primitive earthly life.

09:21.852 --> 09:23.478
Speaking of improving your life,

09:23.563 --> 09:28.191
I've just been reading this article
called Ten Days To A Slimmer You.

09:28.234 --> 09:30.569
Full of wonderful suggestions.

09:30.611 --> 09:34.364
Guys, I don't have time for this.
We have a guest.

09:34.407 --> 09:36.366
A guest? Well, let's go meet him.

09:36.450 --> 09:39.077
Let's not. Lilo's in enough trouble.

09:40.121 --> 09:42.789
- BOTH: Trouble?
- Well, all out of lemonade.

09:42.915 --> 09:48.587
Anyway, I know my sister
is very sorry and didn't mean it.

09:48.796 --> 09:50.797
- Very sorry.
- See?

09:50.881 --> 09:52.549
- But I did mean it.
- Lilo?

09:52.592 --> 09:55.802
Next time,
Mertle Edmonds is going down.

09:55.886 --> 09:57.846
She's going way down.

09:57.972 --> 09:59.889
- (MIMICS CROWD CHEERING)
- (NANI CHUCKLES)

09:59.932 --> 10:01.975
No more pro wrestling for you.

10:02.059 --> 10:05.604
Where is she? Where is she?

10:05.980 --> 10:07.939
- Wow.
- Ai-kapulu.

10:08.024 --> 10:12.611
There's our precious angel, who must
be the victim of a misunderstanding.

10:12.653 --> 10:14.613
- Oh, no, no...
- Where is she?

10:14.697 --> 10:18.658
- Jumba. What are you doing?
- Don't worry. The cavalry has arrived.

10:18.743 --> 10:20.744
- There she is.
- No, no, no, no.

10:20.786 --> 10:24.623
Somebody give this kid gold star,
she's so good.

10:24.665 --> 10:26.124
I don't believe we've met.

10:26.208 --> 10:30.837
This is Uncle Jumba and
I'm Auntie Pleakley. EnchantÃ©e.

10:30.921 --> 10:34.132
On second thought, Kumu,
we should talk outside.

10:34.175 --> 10:36.301
It's not polite to interrupt your auntie.

10:36.385 --> 10:37.886
- Knock, knock.
- David.

10:37.970 --> 10:39.971
How's it, everybody?

10:40.723 --> 10:44.726
You remember my Auntie Pleakley
and Uncle Jumba, right?

10:44.977 --> 10:47.479
- Uh...
- Say something.

10:47.521 --> 10:48.813
Uh...

10:49.440 --> 10:52.317
- Nice hat.
- Why, thank you, David.

10:52.360 --> 10:55.445
See? Uncle Jumba
said it made me look top-heavy.

10:55.488 --> 10:57.447
Aunt Pleakley wanted the truth.

10:57.490 --> 11:01.743
What we want and what we need
are entirely different things.

11:01.952 --> 11:03.328
It's true what they say.

11:03.412 --> 11:05.622
Men are from Mars,
and women are from Venus.

11:06.540 --> 11:07.957
- Nani.
- Yeah? Uh-huh?

11:08.042 --> 11:10.835
You've been stressing,
so I got movie tickets.

11:10.878 --> 11:12.545
Movie?

11:12.672 --> 11:17.133
David, I would love to, really,
but I'm gonna have to rain check.

11:17.176 --> 11:21.513
- That's okay. I understand.
- Great. Thanks for understanding.

11:22.181 --> 11:25.809
I dare you to say that's not flattering,
even on him.

11:25.851 --> 11:28.937
Okay, I'm sure that Kumu
isn't interested in this.

11:29.021 --> 11:31.773
- Nice to be meeting you.
- Au revoir.

11:31.857 --> 11:33.108
Bye-bye.

11:34.026 --> 11:36.695
Boy. Good thing we were here.

11:37.363 --> 11:39.197
I'm not talking to you.

11:39.615 --> 11:42.617
Ha-ha...
Sorry about the relatives, Kumu.

11:42.702 --> 11:45.829
Yeah, sorry. Thanks for coming.
See ya at the competition.

11:46.288 --> 11:47.288
(LOCK CLICKS)

11:48.207 --> 11:50.041
Lilo?

11:56.340 --> 11:58.925
I know you want to be
in the competition,

11:59.009 --> 12:02.554
but your behavior today
makes me think you're not ready.

12:02.596 --> 12:04.806
No. I'm ready. It's just...

12:06.726 --> 12:10.645
Mertle pushed my buttons.
I'll be good. I mean it.

12:10.730 --> 12:15.900
I hope so. If there's any more trouble,
you won't be allowed in the competition.

12:15.943 --> 12:20.071
I promise. There won't be any trouble.
I promise, promise.

12:20.614 --> 12:22.407
I triple promise.

12:23.033 --> 12:25.660
- Okay, then.
- Thank you, Kumu.

12:25.870 --> 12:29.080
You don't have to worry.
I've seen the error of my ways.

12:29.123 --> 12:32.959
I will be good from now on
and be the best hula dancer ever.

12:33.043 --> 12:34.711
You'll see. I can do it.

12:35.045 --> 12:37.005
There's no way I can do this.

12:41.010 --> 12:45.638
Just because my mom was
a great hula dancer doesn't mean I am.

12:45.890 --> 12:51.644
The only thing I know
I inherited from her is, well, Nani.

12:53.355 --> 12:54.355
Yeuch!

12:55.357 --> 12:59.652
What if Mertle's right
and everything I do is gonna be stinky?

13:00.696 --> 13:02.906
Maybe I'm just stinky...

13:03.949 --> 13:05.325
Like cheese.

13:06.660 --> 13:08.119
(MUTTERS)

13:10.623 --> 13:16.211
But my mom was beautiful
like an orchid and graceful like a wave.

13:22.426 --> 13:24.302
I'll never be like her.

13:52.498 --> 13:54.833
You think I can do it?

13:54.875 --> 13:57.460
We do together.

14:01.006 --> 14:02.632
Let's win this thing.

14:02.716 --> 14:04.384
- Okey...
- Dokey.

14:05.261 --> 14:07.136
Hula ideas, take one.

14:07.346 --> 14:09.222
Mummies.

14:09.849 --> 14:11.850
(STITCH MOANS)
Huh?

14:11.892 --> 14:14.519
Amputation.

14:15.020 --> 14:17.021
Vampire bats.

14:17.106 --> 14:18.690
Recycling.

14:18.774 --> 14:20.441
- Gossip.
- (GASPS)

14:20.526 --> 14:22.402
Skydive.

14:22.486 --> 14:23.486
Ouch.

14:24.989 --> 14:27.615
I wonder if Elvis had these problems.

14:28.033 --> 14:29.367
Done.

14:29.493 --> 14:34.372
Okay, everyone,
family fun night is ready to begin.

14:35.291 --> 14:36.666
Everyone?

14:38.460 --> 14:39.794
Anyone?

14:41.297 --> 14:44.257
Guys, family fun night.
Everything's ready.

14:44.341 --> 14:46.217
Let's... What's going on?

14:46.343 --> 14:49.262
We're increasing the flow of blood
to our brains to make us think.

14:49.346 --> 14:52.265
- We've only got one day and 23 hours...
- And 16 minutes.

14:52.391 --> 14:56.269
...to come up with the winning idea,
so please leave us alone to think.

14:56.353 --> 14:57.395
Please.

14:57.479 --> 15:02.734
You'll figure it out, and if you ask me,
it's a perfect time to take a break.

15:02.818 --> 15:04.068
- Pass.
- Pass.

15:04.737 --> 15:08.114
- I said, if you ask me, it's...
- We kinda didn't ask you.

15:08.657 --> 15:10.325
That's it, you two.

15:10.409 --> 15:14.120
I've been cooking for hours
and finally picked up the house

15:14.204 --> 15:17.332
just so we can have quality fun time
like Mom used to.

15:17.499 --> 15:20.418
You're part of this family,

15:20.461 --> 15:24.422
so you are gonna come downstairs
and have family fun.

15:24.548 --> 15:25.548
Fun, fun, fun!

15:25.591 --> 15:26.966
(SHRIEKING)

15:28.844 --> 15:30.595
Is everyone having fun?

15:30.721 --> 15:32.430
ALL: Oh, yeah!

15:32.514 --> 15:34.307
- Great.
- Loads of fun!

15:34.725 --> 15:37.852
- I made sci-fi snacks.
- Yummy.

15:38.020 --> 15:41.147
We have deep-fried Martian cockroach.

15:43.150 --> 15:44.817
Mm. Delicious

15:44.902 --> 15:48.279
- I think I'm gonna throw up.
- Ew. I think someone did.

15:49.406 --> 15:51.199
Uh, Nani, what are these?

15:51.492 --> 15:54.494
Alien eyeball dumplings.

15:54.578 --> 15:56.496
What kinda sick joke is this?

15:56.580 --> 15:58.831
Don't be making her mad. Eat it.

16:01.293 --> 16:02.377
It's good.

16:11.345 --> 16:14.180
- Cockroach?
- I'm too upset to eat.

16:14.598 --> 16:16.140
I'm hula-less.

16:16.308 --> 16:19.018
Aw, I'm sure
you'll come up with something.

16:19.186 --> 16:21.396
Come on. Let's watch the movie.

16:21.981 --> 16:25.650
...are dangerous.
They'll destroy everything in their path.

16:25.734 --> 16:28.069
The authorities are asking all...

16:29.279 --> 16:33.282
- It's a bit redundant, don't ya think?
- Shush. I'm trying to watch movie.

16:34.576 --> 16:35.576
Ew.

16:37.413 --> 16:40.999
(JUMBA BLUBBERING, SNIFFLING)

16:41.500 --> 16:43.292
It's so beautiful.

16:43.836 --> 16:48.756
Nani, I think you did a great job
with family night.

16:49.341 --> 16:52.301
- Psst. I know what your problem is.
- What?

16:52.344 --> 16:56.472
I'm sorry to break it to you,
but your relationship has fizzled.

16:56.682 --> 16:58.766
We've been only going out
for three weeks.

16:58.851 --> 17:00.351
A fizzle is a fizzle.

17:00.769 --> 17:04.689
According to this,
comfort plus time equals boring.

17:04.940 --> 17:06.648
DAVID: I think she's just tired.

17:06.733 --> 17:09.694
- Tired, or tired of you?
- Shh.

17:10.738 --> 17:13.196
I wanted to dance
at your wedding, but...

17:13.240 --> 17:15.532
- Shh.
- Fine.

17:19.288 --> 17:20.913
(LAUGHTER)

17:25.794 --> 17:28.546
- (ZAPPING)
- (STITCH YELPS)

17:29.131 --> 17:31.299
Hmm? Hmm.

17:31.967 --> 17:32.967
Mm-mm.

17:35.054 --> 17:36.387
Ow! Huh?

17:46.940 --> 17:48.107
What?

17:54.406 --> 17:56.699
(STITCH YELLS)

18:00.037 --> 18:01.537
- Ah, Stitch!
- Oh, Stitch!

18:05.125 --> 18:06.584
Stitch?

18:06.668 --> 18:08.586
(JABBERS)

18:12.633 --> 18:13.758
Oh, no.

18:15.260 --> 18:19.806
Jumba, Jumba, slow down!
Where ya going? Include me!

18:19.890 --> 18:21.849
Something's wrong with 626.

18:21.934 --> 18:23.267
- What is it?
- I don't know.

18:23.310 --> 18:24.602
Or won't tell?

18:24.686 --> 18:26.354
Ow! My good eye!

18:27.314 --> 18:29.065
You don't trust me.

18:29.108 --> 18:33.528
Fine. You won't tell me what's going on.
I won't tell you something.

18:33.612 --> 18:38.407
Ooh, what an interesting secret
I have that I won't tell Jumba.

18:38.492 --> 18:40.701
Oh, my, it's a juicy one.

18:40.786 --> 18:43.287
- Quiet, you.
- Okay, I don't have a secret.

18:43.372 --> 18:46.958
But don't shut me out.
Let me in. Let me...

18:47.000 --> 18:49.836
- What's that?
- Is sample of Stitch's fur.

18:51.421 --> 18:53.506
Now we shall see.

18:53.799 --> 18:56.300
(BEEPING)

18:56.468 --> 18:58.219
No. No.

18:58.387 --> 19:00.888
Those idiot police.

19:00.973 --> 19:03.057
I hoped this day would never come.

19:03.267 --> 19:07.311
What are you talking about?
What is wrong with Stitch?

19:09.106 --> 19:13.484
During his creation,
Stitch was never fully charged.

19:13.610 --> 19:15.319
(LAUGHTER)

19:17.823 --> 19:19.407
There is it.

19:20.784 --> 19:23.161
(CACKLING)

19:26.206 --> 19:28.332
(CACKLING CONTINUES)

19:31.503 --> 19:33.045
(COUGHS)

19:33.130 --> 19:35.339
That's not so easy on the throat.

19:36.884 --> 19:41.679
Oh, can it be? Have I done it?

19:42.848 --> 19:43.848
(WHIMPERS)

19:49.688 --> 19:53.107
So cute, so fluffy, even.

19:53.192 --> 19:54.192
(SNIFFS)

19:54.985 --> 19:57.195
Where did I go wrong?

20:00.282 --> 20:02.033
Ha-ha-ha! What a relief.

20:02.993 --> 20:07.288
Your name is 626. Isn't that nice?

20:07.623 --> 20:08.664
(GROWLS)

20:08.707 --> 20:10.458
Oh, I know, I know.

20:10.542 --> 20:15.504
You want to get out and wreak havoc,
but your molecules need to be charged.

20:15.964 --> 20:18.216
That's most important part.

20:21.345 --> 20:23.054
(BLEEPING)

20:25.015 --> 20:28.851
Meanwhile, I've got a surprise for you.
Close your eyes.

20:29.394 --> 20:32.271
No peeking. He cheats already.

20:32.356 --> 20:33.648
Aw, jiggiebig.

20:34.066 --> 20:36.442
- Ta-da!
- (MUTTERS)

20:37.236 --> 20:39.111
If it's too big, I have it taken in.

20:39.196 --> 20:40.655
- (BANGING)
- Uh-oh.

20:40.739 --> 20:44.742
- Open up! Intergalactic Police!
- Is nobody home.

20:45.202 --> 20:47.703
Uh, check is in mail.

20:47.746 --> 20:49.080
(HIGH-PITCHED) I'm in the tub.

20:50.749 --> 20:54.669
You are under arrest
for illegal genetic experimentation.

20:54.753 --> 20:57.213
You idiots, you will ruin everything.

20:57.256 --> 21:00.383
- Oh, no.
- Yeah. Tell it to the Council.

21:00.676 --> 21:02.093
You two, get the evidence.

21:02.177 --> 21:05.471
Stop.
His molecules aren't fully charged.

21:05.597 --> 21:07.098
No, no! No! Oh.

21:07.140 --> 21:09.141
COMPUTER: Warning. Warning.

21:09.601 --> 21:11.602
Electromagnetic bonding incomplete.

21:11.770 --> 21:15.648
No, no,
there's no telling what will happen.

21:15.732 --> 21:17.608
Let me go. No!

21:17.776 --> 21:22.071
What will become
of my little monstrosity?

21:22.614 --> 21:25.283
Now his circuits are going haywire.

21:25.784 --> 21:27.785
That's why he was freaking out.

21:27.869 --> 21:28.995
He can't control it.

21:29.121 --> 21:33.708
If it continues, his circuits will
burn themselves out like supernova.

21:33.875 --> 21:35.710
Can ya...
Can ya fix him?

21:35.794 --> 21:39.630
I must,
or my little Stitch will shut down...

21:41.300 --> 21:42.758
For good.

21:54.479 --> 21:55.855
- (FOOTSTEPS)
- (GASPS)

21:58.025 --> 22:00.401
Stitch? Stitch?

22:07.826 --> 22:08.826
(WHIMPERS)

22:17.377 --> 22:22.631
Once there was a boy with big,
puffy hair who loved meat loaf a lot.

22:24.176 --> 22:26.594
So he put the leftovers
in his pillowcase.

22:27.012 --> 22:31.891
But that night, a buzzard flew in the
window and tried to eat the meat loaf.

22:32.642 --> 22:34.852
Trashed the whole house.

22:35.520 --> 22:38.856
And do you know who that boy was?

22:38.940 --> 22:40.274
- Elvis.
- Huh?

22:40.776 --> 22:42.276
True story.

22:44.863 --> 22:47.573
I think Stitch feel better.

22:47.657 --> 22:50.034
Even Elvis slipped up sometimes.

22:50.202 --> 22:53.871
But he never stopped trying,
and neither can we.

22:56.041 --> 22:57.208
- Elvis!
- Elvis!

22:57.250 --> 22:59.377
(BUGLE PLAYS REVEILLE)

23:12.766 --> 23:14.350
At ease.

23:14.643 --> 23:17.978
When Elvis was in the army,
he got things done.

23:18.188 --> 23:23.401
Here's a map that shows
every place Elvis went to in Kauai.

23:23.568 --> 23:26.737
Our mission, go to these places,

23:26.780 --> 23:30.282
where the King
will give us the idea for our hula.

23:31.785 --> 23:34.120
To the hovercraft.

23:34.871 --> 23:38.249
Thanks to a certain sister of mine,
we'll have to walk.

