24:11.450 --> 24:14.368
They don't really know

24:14.828 --> 24:17.621
I like what I see, I see what I like

24:17.789 --> 24:21.459
It gives me such a glow
Yeah, yeah, yeah

24:21.585 --> 24:27.006
First thing in the morning
Last thing at night

24:27.674 --> 24:33.471
I look, stare everywhere
And I see everything in sight

24:34.806 --> 24:37.975
Stop, look and listen, baby

24:38.268 --> 24:41.645
That's my philosophy

24:41.771 --> 24:44.857
It's called rubberneckin', baby

24:44.941 --> 24:48.402
But that's all right with me

24:48.487 --> 24:51.739
People say I'm wasting time

24:51.823 --> 24:54.992
But I don't really care

24:55.035 --> 24:58.204
I see what I like, I like what I see

24:58.330 --> 25:01.874
It gives me such a glow
Yeah, yeah, yeah

25:01.958 --> 25:05.169
Stop, look and listen, baby

25:05.212 --> 25:08.506
That's my philosophy

25:08.590 --> 25:11.759
It's called rubberneckin', baby

25:11.843 --> 25:13.344
And that's all right with...

25:13.428 --> 25:17.348
This is the exact bench
where Elvis sat in Blue Hawaii.

25:18.808 --> 25:21.018
Oh, yeah. That's him.

25:22.312 --> 25:23.896
I can't believe it.

25:24.022 --> 25:28.734
My butt is in the shadow
of the butt of Elvis Presley.

25:29.528 --> 25:30.694
Oh. Yes.

25:30.987 --> 25:32.446
Okay, Elvis.

25:32.531 --> 25:37.117
We're ready to receive
a great idea for our hula.

25:37.202 --> 25:39.537
(ECHOING)

25:43.333 --> 25:44.542
(CLUCKS)

25:51.132 --> 25:52.841
That's it. I got it.

25:53.009 --> 25:57.221
Elvis is trying to tell us
to do a hula about a chicken.

25:57.264 --> 25:58.264
(SQUAWKS)

26:00.058 --> 26:01.767
No, he's not.

26:03.186 --> 26:06.689
There's plenty of other places
on the map that we can go to.

26:08.233 --> 26:09.942
We better hurry.

26:10.068 --> 26:12.069
Hey, drop it!

26:15.240 --> 26:16.740
Gotcha.

26:17.617 --> 26:19.660
(LILO STRAINS)

26:22.455 --> 26:23.581
Yes!

26:23.790 --> 26:25.040
Whoa.

26:35.510 --> 26:36.760
No.

26:38.138 --> 26:39.805
We're sunk.

26:45.103 --> 26:46.645
(WAILS)

26:58.283 --> 27:01.118
I know it's hard
to keep the faith sometimes,

27:01.202 --> 27:05.289
but if you don't give up on Elvis,
Elvis won't give up on you.

27:14.924 --> 27:16.050
That song.

27:16.134 --> 27:18.385
It's about the Hawaiian goddess Hi'iaka.

27:18.470 --> 27:20.137
Hey! That's right, Lilo.

27:20.180 --> 27:21.764
That's a great story.

27:21.973 --> 27:25.809
Friendship, jealousy,
death by molten lava!

27:25.894 --> 27:28.062
Do you know what this means?

27:29.481 --> 27:32.191
- Thank you, Elvis!
- Thank you, Elvis!

27:32.317 --> 27:34.318
We got our hula.

27:39.491 --> 27:41.325
(TYPING, COMPUTER BLEEPS)

27:45.830 --> 27:47.706
Stupid supercomputer.

27:47.791 --> 27:51.669
I know, Mom,
but Jumba and I have been very busy.

27:52.087 --> 27:54.171
- My mom says hi.
- Yeah, hi...

27:54.214 --> 27:58.050
He's waving.
I can't talk about it, Mom. It's top secret.

27:58.134 --> 28:00.719
- I said I was sorry.
- That's it. That's it!

28:00.804 --> 28:03.055
I have to go, Mom. Talk to you Sunday.

28:03.181 --> 28:06.850
I finished plans for new fusion chamber
that will recharge Stitch.

28:06.935 --> 28:07.976
Way to go.

28:08.019 --> 28:10.854
But we don't have alien technology
to build it.

28:10.897 --> 28:12.231
Way to burst a bubble.

28:12.315 --> 28:17.361
We'll have to find primitive Earth
machinery and just hope it works.

28:17.404 --> 28:20.781
No prob. I can get
all those parts from the house.

28:20.865 --> 28:23.325
- (ALARM)
- JUMBA: Agh!

28:23.368 --> 28:27.371
Stitch is having another episode.
They're getting worse.

28:27.414 --> 28:30.958
Hurry. These parts
are crucial to saving Stitch's life.

28:31.042 --> 28:33.001
Nothing can go wrong.

28:42.971 --> 28:44.388
Target sighted.

28:45.056 --> 28:46.849
Gotcha.

28:46.891 --> 28:49.560
Oh, no, it's you. I mean, hi, Nani.

28:49.894 --> 28:53.063
- What are you doing with the toaster?
- This?

28:53.148 --> 28:55.399
Yeah, interesting question.

28:55.483 --> 28:58.235
- What's going on?
- I was just about to...

28:58.319 --> 29:00.362
We have to hurry to... Nani...

29:00.405 --> 29:02.406
- To make toast.
- Toast?

29:02.449 --> 29:04.408
Making toast. We're making toast.

29:04.534 --> 29:08.078
Toast. Who doesn't enjoy
nice, crispy piece of toast?

29:08.163 --> 29:09.538
Answer, nobody.

29:09.581 --> 29:13.917
And there's so many different kinds.
Rye, sourdough, pumpernickel.

29:14.002 --> 29:17.588
You can put marmalade on it.
Tasty toast.

29:17.630 --> 29:19.381
You don't know what you're missing.

29:19.466 --> 29:22.551
- Care to try some?
- That's okay. I've gotta go to work.

29:23.344 --> 29:24.887
- Oh, and, boys?
- Hmm?

29:24.929 --> 29:27.514
Don't play with the toaster.
(GASPS)

29:29.309 --> 29:31.101
Hi, David. Gotta run.

29:31.144 --> 29:33.771
If you're hungry, we've got toast.
Lots of toast.

29:34.063 --> 29:36.607
- Should I make more?
- Just get rid of him.

29:36.691 --> 29:39.359
- But how?
- You're the Earth expert.

29:41.112 --> 29:42.112
(SIGHS)

29:43.114 --> 29:44.114
Hmm.

29:44.657 --> 29:47.117
David, David, David.

29:48.077 --> 29:50.245
Poor, sweet David.

29:50.455 --> 29:52.456
Trusting, naive David.

29:52.707 --> 29:56.585
- Okay, maybe I do need help.
- You're in good hands.

29:57.253 --> 30:00.130
For 29.95,
you can have the kayak all day long.

30:00.215 --> 30:01.590
But, of course...

30:01.800 --> 30:03.217
Look at her. Tsk. Tsk.

30:04.761 --> 30:08.680
- Doesn't even know you're here.
- Maybe because we're hiding.

30:08.765 --> 30:12.684
Oh, I'm sorry.
Is my relationship dying? No.

30:12.769 --> 30:15.145
Okay, okay.
What you think I should do?

30:15.230 --> 30:17.981
Well, it's obvious
she's taking you for granted.

30:18.024 --> 30:22.444
But she won't if
she sees another woman interested.

30:22.487 --> 30:25.239
- What other woman?
- Whoo-hoo!

30:25.907 --> 30:27.699
- Yeah!
- Have fun.

30:27.826 --> 30:32.162
Oh, my, you're so fascinating and tan.

30:32.747 --> 30:35.165
Whoa! I'm so clumsy.

30:35.792 --> 30:37.543
You've gotta be kidding me.

30:37.710 --> 30:41.296
- I don't think...
- It's working. She's coming over.

30:41.339 --> 30:43.841
- Hey, Nani.
- No waving. Be cool.

30:44.759 --> 30:47.219
Is that a deltoid or a rhomboid?

30:47.303 --> 30:48.595
(GIGGLING)

30:49.138 --> 30:50.347
Okay.

30:50.431 --> 30:52.933
Hey, David, I'm off at 5:00.
Wanna get some dinner?

30:53.017 --> 30:54.601
- Great.
- He has plans.

30:54.686 --> 30:57.896
- He does?
- With me. I'm the new girl on the island.

30:58.147 --> 30:59.565
Let me get this straight.

30:59.649 --> 31:02.359
You came here and interrupted me

31:02.402 --> 31:06.113
to tell me you have
pretend plans with Pleakley?

31:06.197 --> 31:09.032
I, uh, don't know
what you're talking about.

31:09.075 --> 31:12.786
My name is Inga.
I'm a foreign exchange student.

31:12.871 --> 31:14.454
Are you jealous?

31:14.747 --> 31:16.957
Mmm... No.

31:19.085 --> 31:20.669
Well, you blew it.

31:21.045 --> 31:22.045
Aha!

31:33.766 --> 31:35.392
(BOTH LAUGH)

31:40.523 --> 31:42.608
LILO: This is how the story goes, Stitch.

31:43.735 --> 31:47.779
Once, there was a beautiful
goddess named Hi'iaka

31:47.864 --> 31:50.657
and a handsome mortal
named Lohi'au.

31:52.285 --> 31:55.412
They were as close
as two people could be.

31:57.081 --> 31:58.081
Oops!

31:59.417 --> 32:03.253
But one day, Pele,
the volcano goddess,

32:03.296 --> 32:05.631
grew jealous of their friendship.

32:07.926 --> 32:14.848
So she took Lohi'au and threw him
into a volcano filled with molten lava.

32:15.058 --> 32:17.643
- Waagh!
- Oh... Stitch!

32:17.936 --> 32:19.269
My bad.

32:25.026 --> 32:29.613
Hi'iaka discovered his body
in a cavern by a sea cliff,

32:29.697 --> 32:31.448
and she stayed with him,

32:31.616 --> 32:35.202
praying to the gods
to bring Lohi'au's spirit back.

32:37.914 --> 32:39.498
And it worked.

32:39.582 --> 32:41.750
Her love brought him back to life,

32:42.001 --> 32:46.463
proving that love
is more powerful than death.

32:46.589 --> 32:51.510
MAN: I will love you always

32:56.516 --> 32:58.558
We are ready for rehearsal.

33:02.522 --> 33:07.401
KUMU: Okay, girls, this is your last
rehearsal before tomorrow's competition.

33:07.485 --> 33:10.612
What if I forget the moves
and Mertle laughs at me?

33:10.655 --> 33:13.699
And I get mad and pound her?

33:13.992 --> 33:16.660
You gotta help me, Stitch. I need you.

33:16.786 --> 33:18.578
We do together.

33:22.917 --> 33:26.294
Our hula is about an ancient friendship

33:26.337 --> 33:30.048
that proves love
is more powerful than death.

33:30.133 --> 33:31.842
Oh, brother.

33:32.010 --> 33:35.512
The great goddess Hi'iaka... That's me!

33:35.680 --> 33:38.890
And the brave and handsome
mortal Lohi'au.

33:40.935 --> 33:42.394
That's Stitch.

33:48.609 --> 33:52.821
I said, the handsome mortal Lohi'au!

33:55.533 --> 33:57.993
Oh, handsome mortal!

33:58.870 --> 34:00.704
Stink-o-rama.

34:00.913 --> 34:02.831
Stitch, get out here.

34:02.874 --> 34:03.874
(RUMBLING)

34:04.042 --> 34:05.042
(GROWLS)

34:05.376 --> 34:07.961
- What are you doing?
- (GIRLS LAUGH)

34:09.213 --> 34:10.797
Cut it out.

34:11.382 --> 34:13.550
That's not what we practiced.

34:14.469 --> 34:15.677
Stitch!

34:18.014 --> 34:19.264
No!

34:20.933 --> 34:23.268
- LILO: Stop it!
- He's crazy!

34:23.351 --> 34:24.351
(GIRLS SCREAM)

34:26.938 --> 34:28.607
Girls, girls, get behind me.

34:28.690 --> 34:31.902
Lilo, get control of your dog.
Nice doggy...

34:31.944 --> 34:33.820
Lilo! Lilo!

34:33.905 --> 34:35.280
(SCREAMS)

34:42.663 --> 34:46.917
Lilo, you will not be allowed
to rehearse at this halau again.

34:51.839 --> 34:54.299
Lilo, I... I...

35:00.389 --> 35:02.641
NANI: Come on.
It couldn't have been that bad.

35:04.310 --> 35:05.727
It was.

35:05.770 --> 35:07.604
Mahalo. Have a good one.

35:07.647 --> 35:11.691
- You're not listening to me.
- I'm listening. I have to work.

35:12.151 --> 35:17.614
My hula career is falling to pieces,
and you're worried about stinking work?

35:17.657 --> 35:20.075
Stitch needs you to be patient with him.

35:20.118 --> 35:23.120
- He did it on purpose.
- You don't mean that.

35:23.204 --> 35:25.455
You should have seen
the way he was acting.

35:25.498 --> 35:30.877
- Aren't you being overdramatic?
- His goodness level is at rock bottom.

