- Stupid head.

39:32.578 --> 39:34.371
Keep walking.

39:34.705 --> 39:35.705
(STITCH MUTTERS)

39:42.755 --> 39:44.881
Stitch sorry.

39:44.965 --> 39:48.843
We said we were gonna be good.
I needed you, Stitch.

39:54.975 --> 39:57.560
Stitch good again.

40:02.358 --> 40:06.403
If you promise to be good,
I'll give you one more chance.

40:06.904 --> 40:10.907
- But I want you to promise.
- Oh, yeah. (ALIEN LANGUAGE)

40:13.202 --> 40:16.663
You get the costumes,
and I'll get the record player.

40:19.583 --> 40:22.752
Stitch good.
Good, good, good, good, good.

40:23.087 --> 40:24.712
Stitch good...

40:25.464 --> 40:26.840
(WHIMPERS, GROWLS)

40:27.675 --> 40:29.050
(FIZZING)

40:33.389 --> 40:35.140
We are ready.

40:38.269 --> 40:40.228
- Stitch.
- Lilo.

40:40.271 --> 40:43.022
- Everything's ruined.
- I... I sorry.

40:43.107 --> 40:45.608
I don't know why I ever believed you.

40:45.651 --> 40:48.069
Something wrong with Stitch.

40:48.112 --> 40:50.280
I know what's wrong with you.

40:50.364 --> 40:53.867
You're bad, and you'll always be bad.

41:01.625 --> 41:05.170
Three. Two. One. Ta-da!

41:05.254 --> 41:06.963
There it is, Pleakley.

41:07.006 --> 41:10.925
The fusion chamber,
the only thing that can save Stitch.

41:10.968 --> 41:14.137
- It's amazing.
- Just another work of genius.

41:14.305 --> 41:17.223
Oh, oh, can I switch it on?
Please, please?

41:17.308 --> 41:19.476
Oh, no, no, no. No, no, no.

41:19.560 --> 41:22.353
That is extremely delicate machine.

41:22.438 --> 41:24.647
It takes superior mind.

41:29.111 --> 41:31.070
(HUMMING)

41:31.280 --> 41:34.824
Heh, thanks to me, crisis is over.

41:34.867 --> 41:35.867
Oh!

41:38.329 --> 41:40.830
Jumba? Jumba?

41:40.873 --> 41:42.248
What happened?

41:49.256 --> 41:50.256
(METAL SCRAPING)

41:53.135 --> 41:54.844
That's it, Pleakley.

41:55.513 --> 41:56.930
It's over.

41:57.014 --> 41:59.432
I can't build a new fusion chamber.

41:59.517 --> 42:02.185
Sure you can,
like you built the first one.

42:02.228 --> 42:04.521
I didn't build first one.

42:04.605 --> 42:07.732
I ordered it from catalogue.

42:07.816 --> 42:09.150
A catalogue?

42:09.568 --> 42:13.321
And now there is no hope
for my little creation.

42:20.412 --> 42:23.039
Jumba has failed family.

42:23.749 --> 42:26.543
So you didn't build
the first fusion chamber.

42:26.627 --> 42:27.877
So what?

42:27.920 --> 42:31.714
You still built Stitch, didn't ya?
Well, didn't ya?

42:32.132 --> 42:33.341
Yes.

42:33.384 --> 42:36.386
And you're still an evil genius. Admit it.

42:36.470 --> 42:39.556
No, I... I don't like to brag.

42:39.598 --> 42:43.851
Well, see, that's why
you're the only one who can do it.

42:44.645 --> 42:45.687
(COMPUTER BLEEPS)

42:50.568 --> 42:52.902
Pleakley, my wrench!

42:57.616 --> 42:58.866
Lilo?

43:03.330 --> 43:04.414
Hey, Lilo.

43:04.456 --> 43:07.959
I'm not doing the hula with him.
So don't try to make me.

43:08.043 --> 43:09.586
Okay, okay.

43:09.670 --> 43:12.088
He's ruining my chance of winning.

43:12.131 --> 43:15.341
Lilo, baby, it's just a contest.

43:15.426 --> 43:19.387
- No, it's not. Now get off my bed.
- Not until we talk about this.

43:19.430 --> 43:22.432
You're no help! I wish Mom were here.

43:22.474 --> 43:26.144
- I'm doing the best I can.
- Well, it's not good enough.

43:26.228 --> 43:28.187
Don't you think I know that?

43:34.737 --> 43:35.945
BOTH: Oh...

43:47.750 --> 43:48.791
NANI: Hey.

43:48.834 --> 43:52.211
Remember how she would always
make up those funny constellations?

43:52.296 --> 43:54.464
Like Swiss Cheese Man?

43:54.548 --> 43:57.216
Where is the Stinky Bag of Garbage
again?

43:57.301 --> 44:00.053
NANI: Near the Sour Milky Way.

44:00.137 --> 44:02.430
Right, near the Old Lady...

44:02.473 --> 44:04.349
BOTH: With the Chihuahua
on her Head.

44:10.439 --> 44:14.442
I have to win the contest,
just like Mom did.

44:14.652 --> 44:19.656
If I win, she'll know I'm good,
and she'll be proud of me.

44:21.659 --> 44:23.117
Oh, baby.

44:23.160 --> 44:27.497
You don't have to win anything
for Mom to be proud of you.

44:27.790 --> 44:31.542
- How do you know?
- Because I know everything.

44:32.753 --> 44:35.046
Okay, I don't know everything,

44:35.130 --> 44:39.676
but I think Mom would be proud of you
just for being you.

44:41.220 --> 44:42.595
You, too.

44:45.057 --> 44:46.683
Thanks, Lilo.

45:34.898 --> 45:35.898
(WHIMPERS)

45:44.742 --> 45:46.576
Stitch good.

45:52.249 --> 45:54.167
Stitch good now.

46:04.303 --> 46:07.138
(ELVIS WITH JXL:
A LITTLE LESS CONVERSATION)

46:14.980 --> 46:16.606
(LOUD GULPING)

46:17.065 --> 46:18.065
(BELCHING)

46:18.817 --> 46:22.904
A little less conversation
a little more action, please

46:22.946 --> 46:26.491
All this aggravation
ain't satisfactioning me

46:27.242 --> 46:31.204
A little more bite and a little less bark
A little less fight and a little more spark

46:31.288 --> 46:34.791
Close your mouth and open up
your heart and, baby, satisfy me

46:34.875 --> 46:36.375
Satisfy me, baby

46:44.092 --> 46:45.968
Do you think Lilo will show up?

46:46.053 --> 46:49.972
MERTLE: After that rehearsal?
She wouldn't dare.

47:10.911 --> 47:15.164
- Come on, come on
- Come on, come on

47:15.249 --> 47:17.124
Don't procrastinate, don't articulate

47:17.167 --> 47:20.878
Girl, it's getting late
gettin' upset waitin' around

47:21.129 --> 47:25.174
A little less conversation
a little more action, please

47:25.217 --> 47:29.262
A little more bite and a little less bark
A little less fight and a little more spark

47:29.346 --> 47:32.181
Close your mouth and open up
your heart and, baby, satisfy me

47:32.224 --> 47:37.103
- Satisfy me
- Satisfy me

47:43.777 --> 47:47.238
I just wanted to say
I am very proud of all your hard work.

47:47.447 --> 47:50.700
If it were up to me,
you would all win first place.

47:52.744 --> 47:55.538
He's just saying that
so the losers don't feel bad.

47:56.331 --> 47:57.707
Hi, Nani.

47:59.167 --> 48:01.002
Uh, yeah.

48:02.087 --> 48:03.379
Okay.

48:03.463 --> 48:06.340
(TRUMPETING)

48:06.675 --> 48:09.594
Welcome to
our annual May Day Festival,

48:09.678 --> 48:13.347
where one of our little girls
will be chosen alaka'i.

48:13.473 --> 48:17.560
First up is Aleka,
doing the dance of the pineapple.

48:17.728 --> 48:19.729
(APPLAUSE)

48:22.524 --> 48:23.524
(STRAINING)

48:24.985 --> 48:27.361
Ah, that should do it.

48:32.743 --> 48:35.578
What if it doesn't work?

48:36.246 --> 48:37.622
It will.

48:48.508 --> 48:50.801
Ooh, maika'i, Aleka.

48:51.303 --> 48:53.804
Next up is Mertle Edmonds.

48:57.100 --> 48:59.602
It's a gift certificate to my daddy's store.

49:00.395 --> 49:01.395
Hit it.

49:04.066 --> 49:07.485
Legend tells of a man named Karl

49:07.569 --> 49:11.113
who dreamt of offering
authentic Hawaiian collectibles

49:11.156 --> 49:13.449
at an affordable price.

49:13.533 --> 49:17.787
Like this costume
in seven natural colors,

49:17.829 --> 49:23.292
and these genuine faux pearls,
each a jewel of the Pacific.

49:24.711 --> 49:30.675
The best things in life are marked down
for clearance this weekend at Karl's.

49:32.302 --> 49:34.387
Mertle, what can I say?

49:35.514 --> 49:36.847
Thank you.

49:38.141 --> 49:39.475
It's in the bag.

49:40.644 --> 49:44.188
If Jumba and Pleakley don't get here
soon, they're gonna miss Lilo.

49:49.528 --> 49:50.653
No.

49:51.154 --> 49:53.990
- What's happening?
- His circuits are about to blow.

49:54.074 --> 49:56.492
We have to get him
in the fusion chamber now!

49:57.119 --> 49:59.704
- Shouldn't we test it?
- There isn't time.

50:01.665 --> 50:07.003
Next we have Lilo, who's doing her hula
about an ancient friendship.

50:07.087 --> 50:08.379
This is it.

50:10.007 --> 50:12.174
- You'll be great.
- Stitch?

50:12.342 --> 50:15.594
I just want to say I...

50:15.679 --> 50:17.680
I can't talk now. I have to go on.

50:17.723 --> 50:18.889
I know, I...

50:20.017 --> 50:22.601
- Oh, no, badness coming on.
- What?

50:22.686 --> 50:25.479
- I... I have to...
- Are you okay?

50:26.690 --> 50:28.107
Stitch!

50:38.160 --> 50:39.452
No.

50:39.911 --> 50:43.205
- Stitch?
- No, Lilo. Too dangerous.

50:45.625 --> 50:49.045
- Stitch?
- Lilo, it's your turn. Everybody's waiting.

50:59.306 --> 51:02.892
My hula is about an ancient friendship

51:04.269 --> 51:08.189
that proves love
is more powerful than death.

51:11.818 --> 51:14.361
(SINGING IN HAWAIIAN)

51:29.419 --> 51:33.214
I will love you, I will love you

51:39.763 --> 51:41.180
I'm sorry, Mom.

51:46.728 --> 51:48.938
Stitch! Come back!

51:49.439 --> 51:52.358
- Have you seen Stitch?
- We thought he was with you.

51:53.110 --> 51:56.821
- Lilo, baby, what happened?
- Something's wrong with Stitch.

51:56.905 --> 51:58.906
He's malfunctioning.

51:59.116 --> 52:01.117
And if we don't find him soon...

52:07.457 --> 52:08.707
Stitch!

52:09.209 --> 52:10.501
Stitch?

52:10.585 --> 52:13.420
- Oh, Stitch! Where are you?
- Stitch.

52:13.547 --> 52:14.964
You there, brudda, brudda?

52:16.341 --> 52:17.466
Stitch!

52:28.270 --> 52:29.478
No!

52:30.313 --> 52:32.606
Hey, we'll find him.

52:34.693 --> 52:38.445
- We looked everywhere.
- He only has few minutes left.

52:40.699 --> 52:42.783
- The ship.
- The fusion chamber.

52:43.243 --> 52:44.493
Stitch!

53:01.011 --> 53:02.344
Stitch.

53:08.143 --> 53:10.311
- We have to stop him.
- (CAR HORN BEEPS)

53:10.520 --> 53:11.520
Whoo!

53:15.358 --> 53:18.903
- I think I should drive.
- Two eyes. My car. I'm driving.

53:20.572 --> 53:24.742
At the rate he is going, he's soon
to be accelerating into stratosphere.

53:24.826 --> 53:27.703
If only we had way to
communicate with him.

53:27.746 --> 53:32.374
Stitch has taken off in the ship,
and we have no way to contact him.

53:32.417 --> 53:35.252
- Poor Jumba. He's worked so hard.
- Give me that!

53:35.545 --> 53:39.381
Yes, yes... Yes, Mother Pleakley.
He'll call you back.

53:39.424 --> 53:42.843
Hello. Thanks for using
the Uninhabited Planet Index,

53:42.928 --> 53:46.597
your guide to the galaxy's
most isolated and lonely locations.

53:46.681 --> 53:50.935
If your selection is Planet Z-13,
engage hyper-drive.

53:51.019 --> 53:53.896
LILO: Stitch! Can you hear me?
I need you.

53:54.022 --> 53:55.898
Please come back.

53:56.733 --> 53:59.735
Stitch can never come back.

54:06.326 --> 54:09.245
- JUMBA: He's lost control of ship.
- What?

54:18.296 --> 54:20.172
PLEAKLEY: What do we do now?

54:23.843 --> 54:25.928
It was my best hiding place.

54:32.769 --> 54:36.063
Get him into fusion chamber
before his energy runs out.

54:36.106 --> 54:37.690
Is only chance!

54:51.621 --> 54:52.663
No.

54:55.208 --> 54:56.458
Stitch?

54:56.668 --> 54:57.668
(GROANING)

55:06.136 --> 55:07.136
Stitch!

55:10.598 --> 55:13.475
No, Lilo. Too dangerous.

55:13.518 --> 55:15.602
You're not dangerous.

55:17.480 --> 55:20.232
We have to get you
into Jumba's machine.

55:33.371 --> 55:36.874
No worry. I've got you, Nani.

56:00.482 --> 56:03.150
Stitch, you're gonna be okay now.

56:05.236 --> 56:06.695
Please be okay.

56:12.869 --> 56:14.661
Stitch sorry.

56:22.003 --> 56:23.212
Stitch?

56:26.383 --> 56:28.717
Hurry, before... Oh!

56:28.802 --> 56:29.843
No!

56:29.886 --> 56:33.055
Jumba. Jumba, it's not working.

56:33.473 --> 56:34.765
Oh, no.

56:41.398 --> 56:43.065
We're too late.

57:04.921 --> 57:09.258
- No!
- Lilo, wait. There's nothing you can do.

57:11.136 --> 57:12.678
He's gone.

57:13.054 --> 57:14.888
Oh, honey, come here.

57:14.931 --> 57:16.306
No!

57:19.269 --> 57:20.561
Stitch.

57:21.646 --> 57:23.730
I'm so sorry.

57:28.736 --> 57:30.946
I kept saying how I needed you.

57:33.867 --> 57:35.993
But you needed me more.

57:52.302 --> 57:54.094
You're my ohana, Stitch.

57:57.849 --> 58:00.267
And I'll always love you.

58:07.150 --> 58:09.485
(WOMAN SINGING IN HAWAIIAN)

58:13.656 --> 58:18.535
I will love you

58:19.829 --> 58:22.456
(SINGING CONTINUES IN HAWAIIAN)

58:38.306 --> 58:44.937
I will love you

58:47.315 --> 58:50.817
Stitch not bad.

58:51.236 --> 58:52.861
Stitch fluffy.

58:52.946 --> 58:54.029
Stitch!

59:00.495 --> 59:02.788
But how is it possible?

59:02.872 --> 59:04.164
It's not.

59:06.209 --> 59:09.336
Stitch okay now?

59:10.421 --> 59:12.381
No more nightmares.

59:14.092 --> 59:15.551
Stitch!

59:15.593 --> 59:18.262
You look fluffier than ever.

59:18.346 --> 59:20.514
PLEAKLEY: Come here, you.
Group hug!

59:29.566 --> 59:34.861
So Hi'iaka and Lohi'au were reunited
and are together to this day.

59:36.364 --> 59:38.574
Kui ka laima!

59:39.909 --> 59:41.493
Hoo kee ma!

59:41.578 --> 59:43.287
(MAN SINGING IN HAWAIIAN)

01:00:11.232 --> 01:00:12.274
Nani!

01:00:14.652 --> 01:00:16.278
I will love you

01:00:16.362 --> 01:00:19.615
I will love you always

01:00:20.491 --> 01:00:22.492
When it's hard to stand

01:00:22.577 --> 01:00:25.829
Oh, you can take my hand

01:00:26.748 --> 01:00:28.415
And I will love you

01:00:28.458 --> 01:00:32.586
I will love you always

01:00:32.837 --> 01:00:34.463
I will love you

01:00:34.547 --> 01:00:38.175
I will love you always

01:00:38.301 --> 01:00:41.094
Mom would be so proud of you.

